gn variants mapped to audience, channel, and offer","Unstructured guessing without validation","Publishing output without review","Skipping source constraints"],"correctAnswerIndex":0,"explanation":"Campaign variants mapped to audience, channel, and offer is the professional technique for this topic."},{"id":"sales-p1-s3-q3","question":"Which review check best confirms AI Ad and Campaign Creation is ready for a client or stakeholder?","options":["Only checking whether the output looks impressive","Verifying the output against source data, constraints, and acceptance criteria","Removing all logs after a successful demo","Using the same prompt or workflow for every domain"],"correctAnswerIndex":1,"explanation":"Professional AI work needs verification against source data, constraints, and acceptance criteria before handoff."}]}},{"id":"sales-p1-s4","title":"Sales Forecasting Foundations","description":"Understand pipeline stages, conversion rates, seasonality, and forecast hygiene.","estimatedTime":"3 hours","difficulty":"Beginner","learningTypes":["Reading","Practice"],"resources":[{"label":"Google Analytics 4 Reports","type":"article","url":"https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/9304153"},{"label":"Khan Academy Statistics","type":"article","url":"https://www.khanacademy.org/math/statistics-probability"}],"test":{"id":"sales-p1-s4-test","title":"Sales Forecasting Foundations Check","questions":[{"id":"sales-p1-s4-q1","question":"In Sales Forecasting Foundations, which option is the correct technical choice?","options":["Unstructured guessing without validation","Forecast built from pipeline stages and historical conversion rates","Publishing output without review","Skipping source constraints"],"correctAnswerIndex":1,"explanation":"Forecast built from pipeline stages and historical conversion rates is the professional technique for this topic."},{"id":"sales-p1-s4-q2","question":"A workflow for Sales Forecasting Foundations fails because the team used \"Unstructured guessing without validation\". What should they use instead?","options":["Forecast built from pipeline stages and historical conversion rates","Unstructured guessing without validation","Publishing output without review","Skipping source constraints"],"correctAnswerIndex":0,"explanation":"Forecast built from pipeline stages and historical conversion rates is the professional technique for this topic."},{"id":"sales-p1-s4-q3","question":"Which review check best confirms Sales Forecasting Foundations is ready for a client or stakeholder?","options":["Only checking whether the output looks impressive","Verifying the output against source data, constraints, and acceptance criteria","Removing all logs after a successful demo","Using the same prompt or workflow for every domain"],"correctAnswerIndex":1,"explanation":"Professional AI work needs verification against source data, constraints, and acceptance criteria before handoff."}]}},{"id":"sales-p1-s5","title":"Responsible Sales Automation","description":"Respect consent, opt-outs, claims, and human review of outbound messages.","estimatedTime":"3 hours","difficulty":"Beginner","learningTypes":["Reading","Practice"],"resources":[{"label":"OpenAI Usage Policies","type":"article","url":"https://openai.com/policies/usage-policies/"},{"label":"NIST AI RMF","type":"article","url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework"}],"test":{"id":"sales-p1-s5-test","title":"Responsible Sales Automation Check","questions":[{"id":"sales-p1-s5-q1","question":"In Responsible Sales Automation, which option is the correct technical choice?","options":["Unstructured guessing without validation","Compliance and opt-out checks before outbound automation","Publishing output without review","Skipping source constraints"],"correctAnswerIndex":1,"explanation":"Compliance and opt-out checks before outbound automation is the professional technique for this topic."},{"id":"sales-p1-s5-q2","question":"A workflow for Responsible Sales Automation fails because the team used \"Unstructured guessing without validation\". What should they use instead?","options":["Compliance and opt-out checks before outbound automation","Unstructured guessing without validation","Publishing output without review","Skipping source constraints"],"correctAnswerIndex":0,"explanation":"Compliance and opt-out checks before outbound automation is the professional technique for this topic."},{"id":"sales-p1-s5-q3","question":"Which review check best confirms Responsible Sales Automation is ready for a client or stakeholder?","options":["Only checking whether the output looks impressive","Verifying the output against source data, constraints, and acceptance criteria","Removing all logs after a successful demo","Using the same prompt or workflow for every domain"],"correctAnswerIndex":1,"explanation":"Professional AI work needs verification against source data, constraints, and acceptance criteria before handoff."}]}}],"finalTest":{"id":"asm-p1-final","title":"Phase 1 Final: AI Sales & Marketing Specialist Foundations","questions":[{"id":"asm-p1-final-q1","question":"In AI Sales & Marketing Specialist Foundations, what should be defined before a workflow, prompt, model, or dashboard is released?","options":["Only the tool brand used in the demo","Input data, output format, acceptance criteria, owner, and validation method","A promise that the AI will never make mistakes","The color of the final presentation"],"correctAnswerIndex":1,"explanation":"A professional release needs defined inputs, outputs, owners, validation, and acceptance criteria."},{"id":"asm-p1-final-q2","question":"Which signal indicates a quality problem during AI Sales & Marketing Specialist Foundations?","options":["The workflow includes source links and logs","Outputs are confident but cannot be traced to source data, rules, or tests","The project has a rollback or revision plan","The team records assumptions and constraints"],"correctAnswerIndex":1,"explanation":"Confident untraceable outputs are a core risk in AI-enabled work."},{"id":"asm-p1-final-q3","question":"Which artifact best supports maintenance after AI Sales & Marketing Specialist Foundations is handed off?","options":["A private chat message with no context","A runbook or case study with data sources, configuration, tests, and known limitations","A screenshot of the final result only","An undocumented copy of the prompt or workflow"],"correctAnswerIndex":1,"explanation":"Maintenance requires documented sources, configuration, tests, limitations, and ownership."},{"id":"asm-p1-final-q4","question":"When a result from AI Sales & Marketing Specialist Foundations affects customers or business decisions, what should happen before it is trusted?","options":["It should be reviewed against source evidence and domain rules","It should be accepted because it was generated quickly","It should be hidden from stakeholders","It should be reformatted without checking substance"],"correctAnswerIndex":0,"explanation":"Customer-facing and decision-support outputs need evidence checks and domain review."},{"id":"asm-p1-final-q5","question":"Which metric or check is most useful for proving AI Sales & Marketing Specialist Foundations created value?","options":["Number of tools mentioned in the project","Measured accuracy, time saved, risk reduced, revenue impact, or stakeholder task success","Whether the demo used the newest AI model","Number of colors used in the interface"],"correctAnswerIndex":1,"explanation":"Professional AI work should connect technical output to measurable quality, efficiency, risk, or business value."}]}},{"id":"asm-p2","phaseNumber":2,"title":"AI CRM Operations","description":"Build professional skill in ai crm operations with real tools, standards, and deliverables.","estimatedDuration":"2 weeks","weekRange":"Week 3-4","outcome":"You can apply ai crm operations in portfolio-grade work.","access":"locked","sections":[{"id":"asm-p2-s1","title":"AI CR